        <fields>
            <name>Header_Text_0_0_0</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rehabilitation of Offenders Act 1974 declaration: &lt;/strong&gt;I declare that I have no current criminal convictions other than those that are spent under the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act 1974 and, to the best of my knowledge, there are no pending prosecutions against me. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;By virtue of the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act 1974 (exemptions) (Amendments) Order 1984 some positions do not allow convictions to be spent i.e. working with children or the vulnerable and some financial services. If you are applying for such a position and have convictions, please advise your recruiter. Any information given will be held confidentially by us and not disclosed elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identity and Financial Probity Checks: &lt;/strong&gt;It is a requirement of some positions that checks on your identity and credit status to determine suitability are completed and results are passed to Capita. To be considered for such positions, we require your permission to undertake such checks and pass the information on. Any information obtained will be held confidentially and not disclosed other than for recruitment purposes. A copy will be provided to you, on request.&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
